{
  "page": "Urragon IV Greyiron",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\"><img alt=\"House Greyiron.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/50px-House_Greyiron.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/75px-House_Greyiron.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/100px-House_Greyiron.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> King</span><br />Urragon IV Greyiron</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\"><img alt=\"House Greyiron.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/50px-House_Greyiron.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/75px-House_Greyiron.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/16/House_Greyiron.svg/100px-House_Greyiron.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Monarch</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Full name</th><td>\nUrragon Greyiron, Fourth of His Name Since the <a href=\"/index.php/Grey_King\" title=\"Grey King\">Grey King</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/High_King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"High King of the Iron Islands\">High King of the Iron Islands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Predecessor</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Torgon_Greyiron\" title=\"Torgon Greyiron\">Torgon Greyiron</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Heir</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Urron_Greyiron\" title=\"Urron Greyiron\">Urron Greyiron</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Successor</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Urron_Greyiron\" title=\"Urron Greyiron\">Urron Greyiron</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Family</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Dynasty</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\">House Greyiron</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Torgon_Greyiron\" title=\"Torgon Greyiron\">Torgon Greyiron</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">References</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Urragon IV Greyiron</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/High_King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"High King of the Iron Islands\">High King of the Iron Islands</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\">House Greyiron</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Urragon_IV_Greyiron&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Urragon was called upon by his aged father <a href=\"/index.php/Torgon_Greyiron\" title=\"Torgon Greyiron\">Torgon</a> to help him rule the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> in court and council, remaining at his father's side for the best part of five years during war and peace. When Torgon died, Urragon assumed kingship without a <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot\" title=\"Kingsmoot\">kingsmoot</a> and no <a href=\"/index.php/Priest_of_the_Drowned_God\" title=\"Priest of the Drowned God\">priest of the Drowned God</a> denouncing him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Urragon's reign was long but undistinguished. His dying wish was for the high kingship to pass to his great-nephew, <a href=\"/index.php/Urron_Greyiron\" title=\"Urron Greyiron\">Urron Greyiron</a>, but the priests demanded that a kingsmoot be held to select the successor. During the <a href=\"/index.php/Choosing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Choosing\">choosing</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Wyk\" title=\"Old Wyk\">Old Wyk</a>, however, Urron Redhand had his axemen slaughter many of the attendees, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyiron\" title=\"House Greyiron\">his line</a> henceforth ruled hereditarily as <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Iron_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Iron Islands\">Kings of the Iron Islands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_iron_kings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_iron_kings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Urragon_IV_Greyiron&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=